    <div class="abbreviated-post-header"></div>
<div class="abbreviated-post">
    <h4 class="post-name">Whether or not to stop hormone therapy?....</h4>
</div>
<div class="abbreviated-post-header"></div>
<div class="content-list-header"></div>
<ul class="content-list">
        <li class="content-item post-starter">
        




<div class="full-post-header  post-starter "></div>
<div class="full-post-container fiji-full-post-container evolution2-full-post-container"  data-reply-id="87484"  data-thread-starter="true" >
<div class="full-post  post-starter ">
	<a name="87484"></a>
	<a name="87484"></a>
	<div class="post-author">
		<table class="post-author-details-table fiji-post-author-details-table evolution2-post-author-details-table" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
			<tr>
				<td class="post-author-avatar-cell fiji-post-author-avatar-cell evolution2-post-author-avatar-cell">
					<span class="avatar">
													<a href="/members/madhatter1">
								<img src="/cfs-filesystemfile/__key/communityserver-components-imagefileviewer/communityserver-components-selectableavatars-64e6583d-e9be-44d9-a227-06c829b8c238/avatar.png_2D00_32x32.png" border="0" alt="madhatter1" />
							</a>
											</span>
				</td>
				<td class="post-author-user-cell fiji-post-author-user-cell evolution2-post-author-user-cell">
				   <div class="user-name-post-date fiji-user-name-post-date evolution2-user-name-post-date">
						Posted by <span class="user-name">
															<a class="internal-link view-user-profile" href="/members/madhatter1">
									<span></span>madhatter1
								</a>
													</span>
						<div class="post-date">
							<span class="label">
																	on
															</span>
							<span class="value"><a href='/cancer_types/breast-cancer/f/38/t/87484' class="internal-link view-post">27 Dec 2014 10:03 AM</a></span>
						</div>
																	</div>
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
	</div>
	
	
	<div class="post-content user-defined-markup">
					<p>Hi folks..<br />Would be interested in anyone&#39;s experience who has stopped hormone therapy early:&nbsp;</p>
<p>I am considering rolling the dice and stopping therapy after 12 months of aromatase inhibitors (initially with arimidex and now on letrozole).&nbsp; I had secondaries in my lymph nodes in my neck after first diagnosis.&nbsp; </p>
<p>I am a medical scientist and understand that the role of these awful drugs is to strip the body of estrogen, when the tumours have turned out to be estrogen positive (ER+).&nbsp;</p>
<p>I have all the usual side effects of estrogen deficiency - typical&nbsp; of these drugs:&nbsp; night sweats, hot flushes, joint pains, fibromas in my feet, trigger finger, carpal tunnel syndrome, plantar fasciitis, dry skin, vaginal dryness, painful intercourse, swollen hands and feet, sleep problems, weight gain (because it hurts to walk and I am not getting enough exercise) and starting to get short-term memory loss - these are ALL caused by my body not producing any estrogen.&nbsp; I feel about 70+.&nbsp; I&#39;m actually 57.</p>
<p>If I stop, I risk a recurrence.&nbsp; If I stay on the drugs my health may continue to deteriorate as early ageing symptoms pile on.&nbsp; So my quandary at the moment is... do I take a return to better health now in exchange for a potentially shorter lifespan?&nbsp;</p>
<p>At the moment, my choice is better health.&nbsp; I would like to walk and be pain free and after over 20 years of a very happy marriage, I would like my sex life back!&nbsp; I&#39;m lucky that from a medical point of view I fully understand the risks.&nbsp; I have asked my family for their thoughts.</p>
<p>Has anyone else been through this quandary lately?</p>
<p></p><div style="clear:both;"></div>
					</div>

	



	  

