<div class="full-post-container fiji-full-post-container evolution2-full-post-container"  data-reply-id="730617"  data-thread-starter="false" >
<div class="full-post ">
	<a name="730617"></a>
	<a name="730617"></a>
	<div class="post-author">
		<table class="post-author-details-table fiji-post-author-details-table evolution2-post-author-details-table" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
			<tr>
				<td class="post-author-avatar-cell fiji-post-author-avatar-cell evolution2-post-author-avatar-cell">
					<span class="avatar">
													<a href="/members/jmp">
								<img src="/cfs-filesystemfile/__key/communityserver-components-imagefileviewer/communityserver-components-avatars-00-00-11-33-42/4TVPL5EDB2OL.jpg_2D00_32x32.jpg" border="0" alt="jmp" />
							</a>
											</span>
				</td>
				<td class="post-author-user-cell fiji-post-author-user-cell evolution2-post-author-user-cell">
				   <div class="user-name-post-date fiji-user-name-post-date evolution2-user-name-post-date">
						Posted by <span class="user-name">
															<a class="internal-link view-user-profile" href="/members/jmp">
									<span></span>jmp
								</a>
													</span>
						<div class="post-date">
							<span class="label">
																	<a href="/cancer_types/breast-cancer/f/38/t/87484">on</a>
															</span>
							<span class="value"><a href='/cancer_types/breast-cancer/f/38/p/87484/730617#730617' class="internal-link view-post">27 Dec 2014 11:24 AM</a></span>
						</div>
																	</div>
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
	</div>
	
	
	<div class="post-content user-defined-markup">
					<p>Hi MH,&nbsp;</p>
<p>Welcome to the forum. Your question is one that I have been asking myself, the last few months. &nbsp;I am also 57 yrs had a WLE, 4 lymph nodes removed, Rads and then developed Cellulitis &amp; Lymphoedema in operated breast. &nbsp;I have been taking Anastrozole and Ad Cal Vit D 3, since Dec 6th 2013. Also penicillin as a prophylactic since Oct to prevent reoccurrence of Cellulitis.</p>
<p>I &nbsp;broke up with partner of 10yrs around same time as diagnosis and moved cities. I don&#39;t have family except my 90yrs old mum, (who&#39;s emotionally frail), or children, and initial reaction on diagnosis was that I wanted to die, ( extreme shock), then extreme rage against the world of couples and seemingly &quot; happy families &quot; . I did not have an easy childhood, but have achieved a lot despite it. The logical part of me knows that every couple/ family has its own &nbsp;despair but when you feel alone, living alone it is hard to remain positive in the early hours of the morning on Anastrozole!&nbsp;</p>
<p>I returned to full time work with an hour and a half commute each way to a job I enjoy ( redundancy &nbsp;in spring ?), so am on Citalopram 20mg again. I have joined local social groups, health walks, etc BUT only &nbsp;feel energetic about 20% of the time. Also, &nbsp;I have insomnia, painful joints, depression, memory loss, vaginal atrophy, back ache, the thought of being like this for the next 10 years is depressing! &nbsp;Long term, &nbsp;( my mum is 90 &amp; dad died at 90), what is the focus to be, become a Nun?&nbsp;</p>
<p>I went on an Odyssey Holiday in September and one woman 59yrs ( a grandmother), with a similar diagnosis to me, refused to take hormone treatment following Rads. She could not see the benefits ( one of her daughters &nbsp;is a scientist),her partner is 10yrs younger. &nbsp;</p>
<p>To feel 70 + at 57 is illogical in 2014. It would be interesting to know what % of people get a reoccurrence withoutAromatase &nbsp; inhibitors ? I cannot afford to retire until I&#39;m at least 67yrs, if my employment lasts in whichever form that long, I don&#39;t know what the solution is either? What do others think? Thanks for reading. Judith xx</p><div style="clear:both;"></div>
					</div>

	



	  

