	<div class="post-content user-defined-markup">
					<p>Good afternoon. A very interesting thread. I have been taking letrozole now for five months. Immediately I was diagnosed the consultant put me on to letrozole with the words &#39;your treatment starts today&#39;. I then went on to have a &nbsp;WLE and SNB and then a re excision to clear the margins. Up until then though I was HER2+ chemo had not been mentioned but at that point it was because by taking chemo &nbsp;I would also get Herceptin. The increase was said to be 3%. I decided that I wasn&#39;t going to have chemo. I had radiotherapy.</p><br />
<p>With letrozole I have been lucky and had few side effects. These were hot flushes to start with but have now calmed down. I also have some short term memory loss and I suspect carpal tunnel syndrome. The hot flushes were so bad at the start that I did consider not continuing. Personally, I&#39;m OK now. I&#39;m in my mid 60s involved in a lot of voluntary issues and taking a masters degree for fun. I think that if letrozole side effects were spoiling my life I&#39;d stop as I personally am more interested in the here and now than what might be.&nbsp;</p><br />
<p>&nbsp;</p><br />
<p>&nbsp;</p><div style="clear:both;"></div>
					</div>

	



	  

