	<div class="post-content user-defined-markup">
					<p>HI Heather<br />Re: RT; with my medical scientific hat on; if I had the choice between AIs and RT I would take the RT in preference to AIs.&nbsp; For me, RT made a difference of around 10% in the overall survival equation - and since the treatment is localised and doesn&#39;t hurt, it as worth doing.&nbsp; About 4-6 weeks afterwards I suffered from short term neutropenia (my immune system crashed for a week) but it was still worth it.&nbsp; I would think twice before refusing RT.&nbsp; Nowadays the targetting is very specific and it can really help.<br />:)</p>
<p></p>
<p></p><div style="clear:both;"></div>
					</div>

	



	  

