	<div class="post-content user-defined-markup">
					<p style="margin-left:30px;">I was diagnosed in 2009 with breast cancer, 6 months after the sudden loss of my husband of 32 years. I went through a right mastectomy with 7 lymph nodes removed. I was stage 2 hormone&nbsp;receptor&nbsp;positive&nbsp;cancer. After chemo and radiation I was placed on the hormone inhibitor. I had such constant body aches, general malaise, short term memory loss that I decided to discontinue the med. In July 2013 I noticed abdominal distention and went to see my general physician. After a CT scan of the abdomen ,I was diagnosed with Stage 4 metastatic breast cancer of the peritoneum. I am now dealing with fighting this cancer which I feel could have possibly been prevented if I would have stayed on the hormone inhibitors.</p>
<p style="margin-left:30px;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-left:30px;">&nbsp;</p><div style="clear:both;"></div>
					</div>

	



	  
