	<div class="post-content user-defined-markup">
					<p>Morning Briggs / Barb, Good reply to add some balance and to get people really thinking about this mega problem. &nbsp;These AI&#39;s side effects can be many and for some downright evil but if they are keeping cancer at bay if nothing else it proves they work :-/</p>
<p>Would be great if they can develop a tablet that mimics oestrogen without feeding the cancer cells, but until then the prevention treatment is a bit barbaric, like having to be given chemo to get Herceptin to be effective etc &nbsp;:-(</p>
<p>It&#39;s the old Quality over Quantity question. You roll the dice and either get lucky seven or snake eyes - no one can predict how things evolve.</p>
<p>So sorry to read about your mets Barb, hope you are not suffering too much with them.</p>
<p>Take care, G n&#39; J</p><div style="clear:both;"></div>
