	<div class="post-content user-defined-markup">
					<p>Hi Heather, Thank you for your kind and helpful reply:-) &nbsp;You certainly don&#39;t look your age ! I think now 60 is the new 50 or something like that. Everyone these days ( in pubs caf&eacute;s etc) seems to be termed &quot;you guys&quot; . So refreshing to hear &quot;girls&quot;. Ha ha. I have always felt that chronological age is a state of mind.&nbsp;</p>
<p>I would have a think about &nbsp;refusing Radiotherapy. &nbsp;I would advise to wear a good support bra ( not wired), at all times. To avoid the possibility of strain/stress to area and cellulitis or Lymphoedema. Also E45, Aloe Vera to keep area moisturised. &nbsp;</p>
<p>Since Rads finished in Feb 2014, &amp; I developed SEs &nbsp;I find that I have no patience with stuff that pisses me off. In the past I may have tolerated &nbsp;unfair treatment but not any more. &nbsp;I am a member of UNISON and paid a subscription for years. Their intervention helped when I returned to work following treatment.</p>
<p>I think walking each day is so important. It really does help with raising serotonin levels and muscle tone.</p>
<p>I walk a lot more now I no longer live in London. The days are getting longer too, which is good news:-D Look after yourself.</p>
<p>Love Judith xx</p>
<p></p><div style="clear:both;"></div>
					</div>

	



	  

