					<p>Hello Judith</p>
<p>Thank you so much for your kind words:) &nbsp;</p>
<p>As I have posted to Madhatter, I will certainly take your thoughts on board re RT and try to make a wise and informed choice when the time comes. &nbsp;I do wear a sports bra now since diagnosis as I find them much more comfortable and I will take your suggestion on board about wearing one at all times after surgery.</p>
<p>I agree walking is very important and it is important psychologically too. &nbsp;Actually just went out for my walk but it is so icey, I gave up as I do not want another fall by slipping on it:) &nbsp;Glad to hear you walk too and I do understand about being more robust when you don&#39;t agree with someone, I feel like that too. &nbsp;For me it is because I want to be honest and direct and I do not want any &#39;elephants&#39; in the room, ever. Life is too short for dishonesty or hurtful actions from other people.</p>
<p>Take care</p>
