	<div class="post-content user-defined-markup">
					<p>Hi there I am 56 I had a grade 1 tumour which spread to th lymph nodes, I had the &nbsp;usual tratment followed by the hormone therapy, initially tamoxifen which made me really ill so then I tried anastrizole (not sure if I have spelt it right) then exemestane which I stopped for over a year ago due to all the side effects particulary the joint pains and weight gain, &nbsp; severe fatigue, depression and loss of sex drive. I sill havn&#39;t managed to lose all the weight which I gained, I still have the fatigue,depression and no sex drive. My cancer specialist has not really given me any advice as to whether It was right to stop them, the decision has been my choice.Three weeks ago I had an enlarged lymph node on my neck. I am scared have been to see the specialist who was not concerned but said to go back in one month if its still there. I have decided to start taking the tablets again, still don&#39;t know if I am am doing the right thing. Would love to have some opinions.</p>
<p></p>
